A man drowned while swimming in the sea at Blue Lagoon beach in Durban on Saturday afternoon, paramedics said. Netcare 911 paramedics responded to a drowning incident at the Blue Lagoon beach in Durban at 1.25pm, Netcare 911 said in a statement. Reports from the scene indicate that two brothers from Pietermaritzburg went for a swim when one got into difficulty. Netcare 911 paramedics, their rescue unit, and the police search and rescue [unit] arrived at the scene and found that life guards had pulled the man out of the water. Tragically, the man was declared dead at the scene, the statement said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.